cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.ET, cs.PL, cs.SY

This paper presents a novel FPGA-based accelerator for Binary Search Trees (BST), which involves hardware design and optimization techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on the data structure and algorithms used in the design, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Block RAMs (BRAMs) architecture, which is related to the cs.ET (Embedded Systems) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents techniques to decrease stalling rates, which could be related to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category.
